CHANGES FROM SCREENFOOL.LIBRARY 1.4 (20.9.93)
---------------------------------------------
* Memory fragmentation greatly reduced

* Recompiled in SAS/C 6.50: Reduced code size, better optimization
  (including 68040 instruction scheduling)

CHANGES FROM SCREENFOOL.LIBRARY 1.3 (29.8.93)
---------------------------------------------
* Bug removed that sometimes generated an empty display mode list.

CHANGES FROM SCREENFOOL.LIBRARY 1.2 (14.7.93)
---------------------------------------------
* Removed 4 Enforcer hits.

* Supports V39 display database extensions.

CHANGES FROM SCREENFOOL.LIBRARY 1.1 (13.7.93)
---------------------------------------------
* Superfluous code removed

* Library now functions (previously Software Failure $80000004)

CHANGES FROM SCREENFOOL.LIBRARY 1.0 (12.7.93)
---------------------------------------------
* Creation of struct ScreenFoolList for length-knowledge features.

CHANGES FROM SCREENFOOL 1.12U (11.7.93)
---------------------------------------
* Display and screen functions removed from main code of the ScreenFool
  utility and placed in resident library for developer access.

The ScreenFool utility is a front-end to the library functions that permits
a wide variety of functions a la ScreenX. The unregistered version is freely
distributable and can be found pretty near where you found this.
